            (22R)-22-hydroxycholesterol [CPD:C05502];
            (20R,22R)-20,22-dihydroxycholesterol
COMMENT     A heme-thiolate protein (cytochrome P-450). The reaction proceeds in three stages, with two hydroxylations at C-22 and C-20 preceding scission of the side-chain between carbons 20 and 22. The initial source of the electrons is NADPH, which transfers the electrons to the adrenodoxin via EC 1.18.1.6, adrenodoxin-NADP+ reductase.
